    <item>
      <title>aggregations</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/aggregations/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/aggregations/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;aggregations&#34;&gt;Aggregations&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;aggregations is &amp;lsquo;single value&amp;rsquo; that&amp;rsquo;s derived by combining several other value. Like when we use &lt;code&gt;COUNT&lt;/code&gt; to count the total rows of particular column or whole table we basically perform aggregation.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;why-aggregations&#34;&gt;Why aggregations?&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Data stored in database generally stored in raw form. When we need to calculate additional data from that raw data we use an aggregation.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;for ex,&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Select&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; users;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;This query will fetch count of total rows in table &lt;code&gt;users&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;sum&#34;&gt;SUM&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;SUM&lt;/code&gt; aggregation function returns the sum of set of values.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>basics</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/basics/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/basics/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;SQL&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Structured Query language or sql is database which is used to collect data and store it.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;select-statment&#34;&gt;Select Statment&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;Select&lt;/code&gt; statment is most common operation in Sql -often called  a &amp;ldquo;query&amp;rdquo;. Select retrives data from one or more table.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Standard &lt;code&gt;Select&lt;/code&gt; statement does not alter the state of the database.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;select-a-single-field&#34;&gt;Select a single field&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A Select statement starts with &lt;code&gt;Select&lt;/code&gt; followed by the fields you want to retrive&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Select&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; users;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;select-a-multiple-field&#34;&gt;Select a Multiple field&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you want to select multiple fileds specify those fields using commas&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>constraints</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/constraints/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/constraints/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;constraint&#34;&gt;Constraint&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A constraint is a rule we create on a database that enforces some specific behaviour. For example, Setting a &lt;code&gt;Not Null&lt;/code&gt; on a column ensures that the column can not be left empty.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;example,&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Create&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Table&lt;/span&gt; employees (&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;id Integer &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Primary&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Key&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;name Text &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;UNIQUE&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;title Text &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Not&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Null&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;null-types&#34;&gt;Null Types&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In Sql, a cell with &lt;code&gt;NULL&lt;/code&gt; value indicates that the cell is empty. A &lt;code&gt;NULL&lt;/code&gt; is different than zero value.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>crud</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/crud/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/crud/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;crud&#34;&gt;CRUD&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;CRUD is a acronym that stands for &lt;code&gt;Create&lt;/code&gt;,&lt;code&gt;Read&lt;/code&gt;,&lt;code&gt;Update&lt;/code&gt;  and &lt;code&gt;Delete&lt;/code&gt;. These four funtionalites are basic in every database language.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;create&#34;&gt;Create&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;To create a table you can use this statement in sql.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Create&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Table&lt;/span&gt; users(&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;id SERIAL &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Primary&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Key&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;-- Serial data type increment id by one&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;name TEXT &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Not&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Null&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;email Text &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Unique&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Not&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Null&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;object-relational-mapping-orms&#34;&gt;Object Relational Mapping (ORMs)&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;ORM is a tool that allows us perform CRUD operations on database using a trandional programming language. These generally comes in the form of &lt;code&gt;library&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;Framework&lt;/code&gt; that you would use in backend code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Functions</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/functions/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/functions/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;SQL is a programming language and like nearly all programming language it&amp;rsquo;s supports functions.We can use functions and alias to calculate new columns in a query.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;between&#34;&gt;Between&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We can check if values are &lt;code&gt;Between&lt;/code&gt; two numbes using the &lt;code&gt;Where&lt;/code&gt; clause in an intuitive way!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;user&lt;/span&gt;,salary &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; salary &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;BETWEEN&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;2000&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;And&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;80000&lt;/span&gt;;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;This query will return user and salary column from employees table whose salary is between 2k and 80k.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;distinct&#34;&gt;Distinct&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Sometimes we want to retrieve records from a table without any duplicates.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>joins</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/joins/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/joins/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Tags: #sql #queries #joins&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;joins&#34;&gt;Joins&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Joins are one of the most important feature that SQL offers. Joins allow us to make use of relations between tables, In short joins allows use to query multiple tables at same time.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;inner-join&#34;&gt;Inner Join&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The simplest and most common joins in sql is &lt;code&gt;Inner Join&lt;/code&gt;. By default a &lt;code&gt;join&lt;/code&gt; command is an Inner Join.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;![[Pasted image 20241219003303.png]]&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Here is simple diagram of &lt;code&gt;Inner Join&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;on&#34;&gt;On&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To perform a table join, we need to tell database how to &amp;ldquo;match up&amp;rdquo; the rows from each table. The &lt;code&gt;ON&lt;/code&gt; clause specifies the each colums to compare.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>normalization</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/normalization/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/normalization/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;tag: #sql #relationship #queries&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;table-relationships&#34;&gt;Table Relationships&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Relational database is powerful because it allows relations between tables. This relationships helps us to keep our database clean and efficient.A relationship between tables assumes that, A &lt;code&gt;table&lt;/code&gt; which contain &lt;code&gt;foreign key&lt;/code&gt; reference it to another table&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;primary key&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Types of relationships&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;One to One&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;One to Many&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Many to Many&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;one-to-one&#34;&gt;One to One&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;one-to-one&lt;/code&gt; relationship links a single row to single crossponding row in another table which is acheived by defining &lt;code&gt;foreign key&lt;/code&gt; with a unique constraint to ensure exclusivity.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Performance</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/performance/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/performance/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Tags: #sql #queries #indexs #sql_injection&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;performace&#34;&gt;Performace&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;index&#34;&gt;Index&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Indexes in Postgres is powerful mechanism  that helps find data much faster on a large datasets compare to normal query.They allow the database to retrieve specific rows much faster than scanning the entire table.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Index :-&lt;/strong&gt; An index is a data structure that sql uses to quickly locate specific rows in table based on a value in one or more columns.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;how-to-create-an-index&#34;&gt;How to Create an Index&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To create an Index in postgres, use &lt;code&gt;Create Index&lt;/code&gt; statement.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>queries</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/queries/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/queries/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Tag: #sql #query&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;basic-sql-queries&#34;&gt;Basic Sql Queries&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;SQL supports a wide range of quries to manage, retrieve and manipulate data in a database.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;1-data-retrieval-select&#34;&gt;1. Data Retrieval (SELECT)&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Basic Query:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Select&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;table_name&lt;/span&gt;;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;This query retrieve every column from table.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specific Column:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; column1,column2 &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;table_name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; condtion;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;-- example, Select name,id From users WHERE  id = 2&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ordering Results:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Select&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;table_name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Order&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;By&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;column_name&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;ASC&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;DESC&lt;/span&gt;);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Limit Results:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Select&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;table_name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;LIMIT&lt;/span&gt; n;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;2-data-manipulation-insertupdatedelete&#34;&gt;2. Data Manipulation (Insert,Update,Delete)&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Insert Data:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;INSERT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;INTO&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;table_name&lt;/span&gt; (column1,column2) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Values&lt;/span&gt; (value1,value2);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update Data:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>structure</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/structure/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/structure/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;limit&#34;&gt;Limit&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Sometimes we don&amp;rsquo;t want to retrieve every records from a table. For example, It&amp;rsquo;s pretty common to have millions of records in table if we try to fetch all records at once system can crash. That&amp;rsquo;s where &lt;code&gt;LIMIT&lt;/code&gt; clause comes in&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Select&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt; users &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Limit&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;This query will retrieve only 10 records from the table &lt;code&gt;users&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;order-by&#34;&gt;Order By&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;SQL also offer us the ability to sort the results of query using &lt;code&gt;ORDER BY&lt;/code&gt;. Order By keywords sort records by the given field in acending order, OR &lt;code&gt;ASC&lt;/code&gt; for short, or you can sort in &lt;code&gt;DEC&lt;/code&gt; order.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>subqueries</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/subqueries/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/subqueries/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;subqueries&#34;&gt;SubQueries&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;tag: #sql #subquery #query&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Sometimes a single query is not enough to fetch all records we need.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;here, an example for subquery&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Select&lt;/span&gt; id,song_name,artist_id &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt; songs&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Where&lt;/span&gt; artist_id &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;IN&lt;/span&gt;(&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Select&lt;/span&gt; id &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt; artists&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Where&lt;/span&gt; artist_name &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;LIKE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;%Arj%&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;);&#x9;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;subqueries-in-select-clause&#34;&gt;Subqueries in &lt;code&gt;SELECT&lt;/code&gt; clause&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Used to calculate a value for each row.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Select&lt;/span&gt; id,name, &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;(&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Select&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Max&lt;/span&gt;(amount)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;transaction&lt;/span&gt; t1 &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Where&lt;/span&gt; t1.user_id &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; u1.id&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9; ) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;As&lt;/span&gt; max_amount&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt; users u1&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  ;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Here in this query, we are fetching some fields in &lt;code&gt;users&lt;/code&gt; table in which we are trying to fetch max amount according to each user from &lt;code&gt;transactions&lt;/code&gt; table&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;subqueries-in-from-clause&#34;&gt;Subqueries in &lt;code&gt;FROM&lt;/code&gt; clause&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Used as a derived table ( or Common table experssion or CTE)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>tables</title>
      <link>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/tables/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:45279/posts/productive/database/sql/tables/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;tables-in-sql&#34;&gt;Tables in SQl&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Tag : #postgres #sql #alter&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;creating-a-table&#34;&gt;Creating A Table&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To create a new table in database , use the &lt;code&gt;Create Table&lt;/code&gt; statement followed by the name of the table and the fields you want in the table.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;ex,&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sql&#34; data-lang=&#34;sql&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;CREATE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;TABLE&lt;/span&gt; employees (&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;id Integer,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;name TEXT, &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;age Integer,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;salary INTEGER&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Each fields is followed by its datatype&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;alter-a-table&#34;&gt;Alter a Table&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We often need to alter our table If we need to add any further fields or remove any existing field.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
